{
  "stem": "1216.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] painting studio that you mentioned earlier, there were several of the painters that were taken and tortured not in Theresienstadt itself, but in the second fortress, what was called the Little Fortress, which was used as a prison within a prison.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And if you had committed any kind of a crime-- be that stealing a piece of bread or a cigarette, or whatever-- we weren't supposed to have any cigarettes, needless to say.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or in the painter's case, painting the real Theresienstadt, instead of what they were told to paint, they were sent to the Little Fortress and either tortured to death or sent on.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And one of the people to whom that happened is an artist who went by the name of Fritta.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Friedrich Taschlisch, or Taschlisch was his name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Sometimes, instead of Friedrich, he's called Bedrich.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "His son survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was then about three, I think, and he was adopted by one of the other artists, Leo Haas, and they both live in Israel now.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But his-- the father, Fritta himself, did not survive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that was-- he went to the Little Fortress, he and his wife.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I've seen it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've seen the exhibit.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the Martyr's Memorial, as far as I know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's where I saw it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What was unusual to me is that he-- Leschly had managed to paint the real Theresienstadt, cut up the paintings, and hide them in such a way that they were not found until after the war.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that, incidentally, is the real Theresienstadt as I know it, because you can see-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] there's one painting showing people-- children and adults-- gathering around, and grubbing through a sort of a trash heap.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's exactly what Hans and I did for food.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
